records.addlTxt:
2:08 PM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Jack Rieder. Defendant Caprice M Walton in court, in custody. Attorney Anna M Kees in court for Caprice M Walton. 

The Court calls the matter for Status of Counsel.
Attorney Kees presents statements as to why the Defendant is not eligible for SPD representation and states this is the 2nd evaluation. 
Defendant is not eligible for State Public Defender representation. 
The Court goes over the Petition for Court Appointed Counsel paperwork on the record with the Defendant.
Court grants request, repayment at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing December 1, 2022. 
THE COURT ORDERS AN EVALUATION FOR COMPETENCY PURSUANT TO SEC SUA SPONTE.. 971.14(2).  Court orders the defendant be examined by the Wisconsin Forensic Unit.  To be done as an outpatient basis within 30 days. 
The Court tolls the time limits for a prelim hearing and will adjourn the matter.
Review hearing scheduled for December 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Hearing scheduled for November 15, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

2:40 PM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Julian Marrufo. Defendant Caprice M Walton in court, in custody.  Attorney Steven Hughes in court for Caprice M Walton. Attorney appears as friend of the court. 

The Court calls the matter for Status of Counsel.
Defendant is not eligible for State Public Defender representation. 
Defendant requests the court appoint counsel.  Court swears defendant.  The Court goes over the Petition for Court Appointed Counsel form with the Defendant on the record.  Court denies request, the Defendant not deem indigent. 
Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.
Hearing scheduled for November 1, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant is not eligible for State Public Defender representation. Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint.
